public class IdBasedNamedGraphSetImpl
extends NamedGraphSetImpl

Named graph set that is particularily well suited for the Semantic Web client. Uses specific graph implementations that are optimized for read-only access. Furthermore, during the execution of triple pattern queries these graph implementations use identifiers for RDF nodes instead of the nodes themself.

Author:
Olaf Hartig

IdBasedNamedGraphSetImpl

public IdBasedNamedGraphSetImpl(IdBasedNamedGraphSetImpl template)
Creates a set of identifier-based named graphs by copying the given set. This constructor copies the given set but it does not create a new IdBasedNamedGraph object for each named graph. Instead, it simply copies the references to the graphs as given in the given set.
